50|$|The {{process begins}} using giant blocks of Chicago's own Blommer chocolate, melted at nearly 200 °F. Tiny {{rectangular}} molds receive {{the combination of}} milk and dark chocolate, plus a special mint oil, after the mixture is tempered to 83 °F. Air bubbles are eliminated by shaking the molds. The product is cooled via a trip through a long, refrigerated tunnel. The chocolates are then sent through an <b>enrobing</b> <b>machine,</b> where more chocolate is poured over them. The Frango mints are cooled once again, then boxed by hand, sealed, wrapped and packaged for shipment.|$|E

